briefTitle: Efficacy Study of Granulocyte-macrophage Colony Stimulating Factor (GM-CSF) for Use in Human IVF
officialTitle: The Effect of Granulocyte-macrophage Colony Stimulating Factor (GM-CSF) During in Vitro Culture of Human Embryos on Subsequent Implantation Rates.
summary: This study is to assess whether addition of 2 ng/ml GM-CSF into a specific culture medium will increase the chance of a pregnancy after in vitro fertilisation.

primaryOutcome.timeFrame: Approximately 5 weeks from oocyte pick-up (corresponding to 7 weeks from ovulation)
